			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=1955')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&amp;TOPIC_ID=6031&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=A+Proposal+I+sent+to+the+Everquest+Dev%2E+corner%2E"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> Hi all, </P><P>I just sent this proposal to Verant and was wondering what you all think. </P><P>----------------------------------------------------------------------<BR>To whom it may concern,</P><P>First off Id like to say that I am somewhat pleased so far with the caster balancing. I think the Everquest development team has implemented some excellent ideas over the past few years that have resulted in a much better game.</P><P>The concern that I have are the post 51 level necromancer spells that require an essence emerald to cast. The concern that I have is for one it is very difficult to obtain Essence emeralds and out of the 3 spells that require them only 1 really justifys use of an essence emerald. </P><P>The spells that I am referring to are Convergence, Infusion, and Trucidation. Currently and I think I can speak for most necromancers here is that no one in their right mind would waste an essence emerald on either Infusion (which gives the necro 1000 mana) or Trucidation (which is a 1100 hitpoint Lifetap at level 60). What if we were to lower the cost of both Infusion and Trucidation to a Tiny Jade Inlaid Coffin, which runs about 75pp. And at the same time change the cost of Convergence (which resurects a player with 93% exp) to a Coffin which runs 150pp. Now while the cost of a coffin is significantly lower and easier to obtain then an Essence emerald, the Necromancer will only be able to hold so many as it is a nonstackable item and takes a full inventory slot as it acts as a container. This will make it more of a special purpose spell and in no way is it unbalanced.</P><P>I hope you find this post in no way is a flame but just trying to see if we can find a more logical use with these spells.</P><P>----------------------------------------------------------------------</P><P>Anyways guys I am looking for some feedback here as to what everyones views are on these 3 spells and if this is a step in the right direction.</P><P><BR> </font></td>

      </tr>

