        <td bgcolor="black" colspan="2"  valign="top">
		<a name="54179"></a>
		<img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;07/29/2002&nbsp;:&nbsp; 23:15:43</font>

		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&amp;id=782"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=782')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=54179&amp;TOPIC_ID=6031&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=A+Proposal+I+sent+to+the+Everquest+Dev%2E+corner%2E&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I have thought this over somewhat.  Here are some of the issues I see with Essence Emeralds that I hope are corrected:</P><P>1. Sacrifice: This spell needs to work on level 60's.  Previously, the argument against this was that level 60's need no more EXP therefore it's a "free" sacrifice.  That argument is not only flawed in the respect that level 60's still die and lose exp and thus must exp to stay 60, but also in the respect that nowadays we have AAXP, which defeats the argument of level 60's having "no need" of EXP. </P><P>2. Trucidation: No one would use this spell in its current incarnation, nor should they.  There are two suggestions I have for this spell.  One using up Essence Emeralds, the other not using Essence Emeralds. </P><P>Using EE: Trucidation should be the Ultimate Lifetap, costing 0 mana and doing 3k of damage, with the possibility of criticals.  It needs to be unresistable, and have a 10 min recast time so people can't abuse it by chaining the spell.  Its cast time should be near instantaneous, so that it is the perfect follow-up after a Lifeburn.  We're talking about an EE here - something that costs either half an hour of power leveling a mule or 300-500 pp EACH time you cast it.  The spell resulting from that _should_ be powerful.</P><P>Not using EE: I propose Trucidation as an upgrade to Deflux, just as ToN is an upgrade to our level 49 drain.  Trucidation, following in the footsteps of Deflux, should cast just as fast, and be 68% more powerful. (calculated from the relative increase in power of ToN over our level 49 lifetap over a 10 level interval, which works out about 113%, and then superimposing that ontop of a 6 level interval)  Thus, assuming the same ratio as Deflux, Trucidation should do 554 damage for 332 mana.  Since Trucidation is a higher level spell, I think 554 damage for 310 or 320 mana shouldn't be out of the line.  The recast time, in this case, should of course be removed.  </P><P>3. Infusion: This spell restores 1000 mana for the cost of an essence emerald.  In its present condition, no one will use it, because 1000 mana is hardly worth losing an EE over.  What I propose for this spell is also two-fold, with EE and without EE:</P><P>With EE: A complete heal ontop of a complete mana heal, castable only once every 10 mins, costs one EE, and castable on anyone, with 10 sec cast time.  This would make sense, as the life of another was sacrificed in order to bring vitality and power to the receiver.  Would do what the sacrifice line was meant to do - provide momentary power at a great cost.  It will allow necros to save groups and raids in case a key class, such as a cleric, is in trouble, or if one mana burn will take out the mob and every wizard is OOM.  It will also allow the necro do what he normally can't in that it gives him essentially twice as many hps and twice as much mana.  It will not come into direct conflict with Trucidation because Trucidation saves TIME, while Infusion is for those circumstances where time is not as big an issue, but resources are.  The complete heal is there so that the spell is not caster-centric, in that it could save tanks too, but not replace clerics.</P><P>Without EE: I like the idea many people had about using a cheaper component for the same effect.  Requiring no component would infringe on the wizard harvest line too much, but considering the fact that we are supposed to be the master of mana regen, not wizards, I don't think it'd be too much if we had a 1000 mana boost every 10 minutes, seeing as how it'd eat a slot from our already over-filled spell slots.  Perhaps make it a DoT mana heal instead of instant to not infringe on wizardly might, and possibly make it require, but not consume, an EE.</P><P></P><P>Etadanik the Redeemed<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
